The code changes do what they say - and are clearly an improvement.

However, the left/right terminology contradicts the naming convention (I think, at this time of the evening, I'm not 100% sure any more).

Wait: per the naming convention, this should be `mk_right_inj`, right?
> An injectivity lemma that uses "left" or "right" should refer to the argument that "changes". For example, a lemma with the statement a - b = a - c â†” b = c could be called sub_right_inj.
Actually: are you sure this lemma should be named "left"? This seems to contradict the naming convention (see below).
I think this one was right before (no pun intended): the left argument changes, so this should be called mk_left_injective, I think. (And otherwise, this lemma were missing a deprecation.)

pullRequest.title: chore: rename injectivity of `Prod.mk` lemmas
